Molecular diagnostics, DNA and RNA extraction, measurement of DNA/RNA quality and concentration, allele specific PCR, Sanger sequencing, mutation analysis using RFLP, analysis of eukaryotic RNA, relative and absolute quantification using real time PCR, Western blot analysis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Goal of the practical course is to give the experimental experience of the previously studied methods (in BGMR.01.001 course).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the students are expected: To be familiar with main research methods in today's molecular biology and gene technology (isolation and purification of DNA and RNA, molecular diagnostics, PCR, sequencing, RT-PCR) and can use these methods for practical applications. To know and apply in practice methods for quantifying and measuring the quality of nucleic acids. To be familiar with basics of data analysis and databases and knows how to use them in practice.
